<h2>What the Numbers Actually Mean</h2>
<p>A correlation coefficient of 0.28 sounds impressive when you are selling software. In statistical reality, it explains about 8% of the variance in rankings. That means 92% of what determines your position has nothing to do with your content score.</p>
<p>To put this in context, here is how 0.28 compares to other correlations in SEO:</p>
